In a relatively well-run town like Stellenbosch in the Western Cape, its Home Affairs is close to collapse, reportedly operating with a staff capacity of less than 15%. The office shares consistent problems with other Home Affairs offices across the country. South Africa has illusions of grandeur about being a modern, competitive country. A day or two or three in a queue at a Home Affairs office in Johannesburg should quickly (well, slowly) disabuse you of that notion. This is a story written while waiting in one of those lines. ‘Most of us have been standing here since 3am’ says 60-year-old man.